710066f-b.text:
8th Avenue, north from W. 13th Street, showing the new County Trust Company Building at the N. E. corner of W. 14th Street. At the right is Greenwich Avenue and its cleared corner. Buildings here were demolished for a work shaft to the subway construction underground. Later this will be leased for a parking lot. A white ventilator building will be erected at the extreme right of same. This structure is not shown in View 2. The 2-story taxpayer on the
8th Avenue side has just been completed.
In the background appears the New York Telephone Building on W. 17th Street and the Empire State Building (under construction in
view 1).
October 13, 1930
July 30, 1932
P. L. Sperr

710065f-b.text:
Eighth Avenue, west side, from W. 13th (right) to Horatio Streets as viewed westward from Jackson Square, showirg the base of a triangular block that has W. 4th Street on its undisclosed side. VView 2 is an oblique view southward from W. 13th Street. No. 3 is detailed to show the new gas station at the 5. W. corner of W. 13th Street. This replaced the structure there as shown in the earlier view. Buildings on the rirht face on the south side of W. 13th Street and extend from 8th Avenue to W. 4th
Street.
View 1: February 14, 1932
View 2: June 24, 1933
View 3: April 9, 1940
P. L. Sperr

710067f-a.text:
Eighth Avenue, west side, from W. 13th to 14th Streets as photograohed from atop the apartment house, No. 2 Horatio Street. At the right is 14th Street with its two bank buildings. Clearly shown is the former New York County National Bank at the S. E. corner. This institution was absorbed by the present Manufacturers Trust Coapany. Partially seen is the New York Savings Bank at the
N. W. corner.
View 2 is the same locale, minus the aforementioned corner
structures.
March 16, 1933
February 14, 1933
P. L. Sperr
